Class DungeonInstance

java.lang.Object
Room
Dungeon
DungeonInstance
public class DungeonInstance extends Dungeon
ASCII ADVENTURER Caden Finley Albert Tucker Grijesh Shrestha The DungeonInstance class represents an instance of a dungeon in the ASCIIADVENTURER game. It extends the Dungeon class and includes additional properties and methods specific to a dungeon instance.

This class includes information about the enemies, items, and state of the dungeon, such as whether it has been completed or visited, and whether the map has been revealed. It also includes the names of the dungeon and its save file, as well as the types of the boss and mini-boss present in the dungeon.

Example usage:

     List enemies = new ArrayListinvalid input: '<'>();
     List items = new ArrayListinvalid input: '<'>();
     DungeonInstance dungeon = new DungeonInstance(enemies, items, false, false, false, "Dungeon1", "Save1", "MiniBoss1", "Boss1", 10);

      Parameters:
      enemies - List of enemy types present in the dungeon.
      items - List of items available in the dungeon.
      completed - Indicates whether the dungeon has been completed.
      visited - Indicates whether the dungeon has been visited.
      mapRevealed - Indicates whether the map has been revealed.
      dungeonName - The name of the dungeon.
      dungeonSaveName - The save name of the dungeon.
      currentMiniBoss - The type of the mini-boss in the dungeon.
      currentBoss - The type of the boss in the dungeon.
      numberOfEnemies - The potential number of enemies in the dungeon.
